From: konfig <konfig@local>
Subject: [PATCH] snmalloc MODULE.bazel: drop dev_dependency on crate_universe

The fork's BUILD files reference `@crates//:flate2` unconditionally
(see snmalloc-rs/BUILD.bazel for the `:snmalloc_rs_profiling` target),
but the matching crate_universe extension is registered with
`dev_dependency = True`. Bazel skips dev_dependencies of non-root
modules, so consumers depending on `:snmalloc_rs_profiling` analyze-
fail with `No repository visible as '@crates' from repository
'@@snmalloc+'`.

Flip the flag so `@crates` is visible to downstream consumers.

This patch is applied locally via `git_override(patches=...)` in
konfig's MODULE.bazel; the upstream fix is tracked in CU-86aj2dujv.

--- a/MODULE.bazel
+++ b/MODULE.bazel
@@ -45,7 +45,7 @@
 crate = use_extension(
     "@rules_rust//crate_universe:extension.bzl",
     "crate",
-    dev_dependency = True,
+    dev_dependency = False,
 )
 crate.spec(
     package = "flate2",
